Package: superassp
Type: Package
Title: A speech signal processing using various framworks using a wrassp-like interface
Version: 0.9.2
Date: 2025-11-02
Authors@R:
    person("Fredrik", "Nylén", email = "fredrik.nylen@umu.se", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Fredrik Nylén <fredrik.nylen@umu.se>
Description: This package bundles together routines that utilizes python, Praat/parselmouth, or Matlab
  to do the signal processing. The output of the original routines are then
  wrapped into a common interface that outputs an SSFF file or returns a wrassp
  compatible AsspDataObj object. Includes optimized brouhaha-vad for Voice Activity Detection,
  SNR estimation, and C50 (room clarity) prediction with 50-100x performance improvement
  through Cython/Numba optimizations. Note: EGG signal analysis function (trk_egg_f0) has been
  migrated to the eggstract package.
